channel.title: Look what I dug up on wikipedia
channel.description:
Found this article, there's a section on rs private servers. http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Articles_for_creation/2006-06-21
Runescape Private Servers For Long RuneScape has been a leading MMORPG in the world of gaming. For the past year or so people have found a way to crack the runescape client (the program that connects to the game server). These versions of the game are not exactly like runescape but are identical in many ways. They share the exact same game engine and map. They also share the same NPCs (Non-Player Characters e.g. Goblins and Demons) and Objects. The only difference the server-side things such as what happens when you click a certain button. Some examples of this is that on a base private server you will not have quests and so forth. You will also not have registering accounts through the internet. To create an account on a private server you must type in the username and passwords in the appropriate boxes in the modified client. This client can be obtained at http://www.moparisthebest.com/moparscape.html. Servers are connected to through ip addresses. The first person to discover servers and edited the client goes by the name WinterLover. The First public server ever was WinterScape. The best servers of all time are BombScape, CheezScape, WhiteScape, and Avatar. Those servers got the closest to being like RuneScape by making quests, full magic, full of all statistics. The owner of those servers were Bomb, XeroCheez, WhiteFang, and Phate. They coded them all by themselves.
It lists bombscape,whitescape,cheezscape and avatar and even gives credit to xerocheez, bomb, whitefang and phate.
